## Context

The 0289 overlap probe found 11 unique climate finance works never captured
by any source. Diagnosis (`deliverables/data-paper/revision-rdj26561/
prior-mappings-overlap.md`, section "Why the never-captured escaped"): 7 of
11 entered OpenAlex after our last harvest (2026-03-22) via retroactive
repository backfills; the other 4 were indexed but invisible at harvest
time (metadata backfilled later, or tier filtering at extraction). The
snapshot decays even for its own period; the fix is process, not a
hand-completed result list.

## Relevant files

- `scripts/harvest/catalog_openalex.py` — incremental machinery exists
  (`from_created_date`, per-query state in
  `data/pool/openalex/_query_dates.json`)
- `deliverables/data-paper/revision-rdj26561/probe_prior_mappings_overlap.py`
  — the recall probe to institutionalize
- `tests/test_corpus_acceptance.py` — where a recall gate would live
- Tracker 0274 / corpus-v2 track (0288) — process home

## Actions

1. Cadence the incremental OpenAlex harvest in the v2 runbook (quarterly
   or per corpus rebuild), using the existing `from_created_date` state.
2. Add a periodic `from_updated_date` catch-up pass: `from_created_date`
   alone misses works whose metadata (abstract) was enriched after our
   pull — one of the two observed escape channels.
3. Promote the 0289 probe to a corpus-validate acceptance metric:
   discovery recall >= 95% against the prior mappings' published queries
   (external ground truth, independent of our vocabulary). Threshold in
   config, not hardcoded.
4. Do NOT inject the 11 missed DOIs directly; they re-enter through the
   normal harvest + filter funnel (part of the tail is noise: duplicated
   backdated Zenodo deposits).

## Test

- Recall-gate test on fixture populations (already unit-tested matching in
  tests/test_prior_mappings_probe.py; add the threshold logic test).

## Verification

- [ ] v2 runbook names the harvest cadence and the updated-date pass
- [ ] corpus-validate includes the discovery-recall metric

## Invariants

- Phase separation (no API calls from Phase 2+); make corpus/corpus-sync
  only; acceptance thresholds never weakened silently.

## Exit criteria

- [ ] Incremental harvest cadence documented and applied to the v2 build
- [ ] Discovery-recall gate active in corpus acceptance
